Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_proto_design_mode(25.10)                      set_proto_design_mode(25.10)

Name
       set_proto_design_mode  -  Controls certain aspects of how the proto_de-
       sign command generates an initial floorplan

Syntax
       set_proto_design_mode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-cover_fixed_macros {true | false}]

       [-effort {low | high}]

       [-flexmodel_constraint_type {guide |region |fence}]

       [-keep_guide {true  | false}]

       [-place_macro {true | false}]

       [-remove_overlap {true | false}]

       Controls certain aspects of how the proto_design command  generates  an
       initial  floorplan. Use the get_proto_design_mode command to return the
       current settings for the set_proto_design_mode command.

Parameters
       -cover_fixed_macros {true|false}
              When enabled it forces flexModel to cover fixed macros that  be-
              long to it when using the proto_design command.

               Default: false

              Data_type: bool

       -effort {low | high}
              Specifies the effort level used by the proto_design command.

               Default: low

              Data_type: bool

       -flexmodel_constraint_type {guide | region | fence}
              Specifies  the  type of constraint the FlexModel is converted to
              after proto_design.

              Default: region

              Data_type: enums={guide region fence}

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation  for  each  set_proto_design_mode parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

               man set_proto_design_mode

       -keep_guide {true|false}
              Retains module guides after the floorplan has been created.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -place_macro {true|false}
              Specifies if macro placement is done when using the proto_design
              command.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -remove_overlap {true|false}
              Specifies if overlap should be removed when using the  proto_de-
              sign command.

              Default: true

              Data_type: bool

       -reset Restores  all parameters modified using set_proto_design_mode to
              their default settings. The -reset parameter must be  the  first
              parameter  specified. If you specify -reset by itself, the soft-
              ware resets all set_proto_design_mode parameters  to  their  de-
              fault  values. If you specify parameters after -reset, the soft-
              ware resets only those parameters to their default values.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

Examples
       The  following  command  runs  the prototyping module/macro placer with
       congestion aware setting:

       set_proto_design_mode -effort low

       proto_design

